underlying_goal: Find the root cause of the Serena dashboard auto-opening and create a plan to fix it.
primary_success: Successfully used the 'systematic-debugging' skill to trace the issue from a generic symptom (browser opening) to a specific root cause (a local dashboard started by an MCP server) and found the exact CLI flag to disable it.
brief_summary: The user reported the Serena dashboard was auto-opening. Claude activated its systematic debugging skill, methodically investigated potential causes, and correctly identified that Serena's MCP server was starting a local dashboard. It then found the correct CLI flag (`--open-web-dashboard`) to disable the behavior and created a detailed implementation plan.
